    <string name="this_begeing_idea">Simply, this is how the idea started!</string>
    <string name="this_begeing_idea_decp">" It all sparked from a passion back in 2021! I stumbled upon a YouTube tutorial on designing Quranic verse images using a phone. The process was quite a juggle: one app for image editing (maybe Picsart, I recall), another for copying verses, then hunting down and installing Quranic fonts – often a paid feature. I just knew there had to be a simpler, more inspiring way!&lt;br/>&lt;br/> That spark ignited the idea for Karmous Quranic Image Designer, bringing everything together: powerful design tools and the complete Quran, all in one app.&lt;br/>&lt;br/> The dream grew with Asaloun Quranic Video Designer, and now, we’re thrilled to introduce NurMontage! It makes video creation a breeze with ready-to-use templates, inspired by the amazing things our users request and create. It’s an ongoing journey of creativity, all for you! "</string>
    <string name="this_begeing_idea_decp_last">"Back in 2021, I watched a YouTube video about how to design a picture with Quran verses using a phone. The method was like this: use an app for writing on photos (maybe Picsart, I don't remember) + a Quran app to copy verses and paste them into Picsart + search Google for Quran fonts and download them to Picsart (I think this feature was paid). Then you were ready to design and share a picture with Quran verses. It was a bit difficult.

From this, the idea for Karmous App for Designing Quran Images was born – everything you need in one app: design tools + the complete Quran in the app. After that came Asaloun App for Designing Quran Videos, and now NurMontage, also for videos, but with popular templates chosen by users."</string>
